WEBVTT

00:41.108 --> 00:43.542
      [SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

02:13.200 --> 02:14.299
       WOMAN: [WHISPERING]
        <i> Come back to me.</i>

02:14.301 --> 02:16.201
             [GASPS]

02:16.203 --> 02:19.538
       [BREATHING HEAVILY]

02:43.664 --> 02:46.498
        [BIRDS CHIRPING]

02:47.568 --> 02:50.636
   [SOFT PIANO MUSIC PLAYING]

03:18.499 --> 03:23.502
     JACK: <i> Beautiful, Addie,</i>
 <i> I never wanted to leave you.</i>

03:28.275 --> 03:30.475
        <i> Please do this</i>
       <i> one thing for me.</i>

03:31.912 --> 03:37.549
   <i> Please find these people,</i>
     <i> Dixie and Jimmy Riggs.</i>

03:37.551 --> 03:40.519
<i> They're in Ransom, California.</i>

03:40.521 --> 03:43.655
 <i> All that gold we looked for,</i>
      <i> I think it's there.</i>

03:46.994 --> 03:48.894
  <i> Don't be saddened by death.</i>

03:53.534 --> 03:55.567
<i> We think it's the end of life,</i>

03:56.837 --> 03:59.905
          <i> but really</i>
   <i> it's just the beginning.</i>

03:59.907 --> 04:03.342
  [SOFT DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

04:09.316 --> 04:13.252
 Daddy left a safety deposit box
       for me at the bank.

04:14.021 --> 04:15.887
       That's no surprise.

04:17.423 --> 04:19.925
 You two with all your secrets.

04:20.928 --> 04:22.427
      Why do you say that?

04:24.431 --> 04:26.898
         Well, he didn't
    leave it for me, did he?

04:35.376 --> 04:39.044
      He asked me to visit
      somewhere, a desert.

04:56.964 --> 04:58.330
              Mom?

05:03.771 --> 05:05.370
    Do you know those people?

05:25.959 --> 05:27.959
      JACK: <i> I'm sorry you've</i>
    <i> never been able to know</i>

05:27.961 --> 05:29.328
   <i> what plagues your mother.</i>

05:30.064 --> 05:32.064
 <i> She is a very broken person.</i>

05:33.434 --> 05:35.000
     <i> I tried to help her</i>
        <i> over the years,</i>

05:35.002 --> 05:37.035
   <i> but now that time is up.</i>

06:17.678 --> 06:19.444
       WOMAN: [WHISPERING]
        <i> Come back to me.</i>

06:19.446 --> 06:22.514
   [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

07:06.627 --> 07:09.027
   <i> ¶ For an abandoned memory</i>

07:09.029 --> 07:11.863
        <i> ¶ That could've</i>
        <i> kept me company</i>

07:11.865 --> 07:16.601
     <i> ¶ In a time of light</i>

07:17.771 --> 07:20.772
        <i> ¶ The ghost town</i>
      <i> that's inside of me</i>

07:20.774 --> 07:23.809
 <i> ¶ The spirits that divided me</i>

07:23.811 --> 07:28.513
  <i> ¶ The dark and its delight</i>

07:29.850 --> 07:34.586
 <i> ¶ I didn't mean to leave you</i>

07:34.588 --> 07:39.658
  <i> ¶ Where the shadows fall ¶</i>

07:39.660 --> 07:41.927
        [WIND WHOOSHING]

08:28.609 --> 08:31.676
  [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

09:13.320 --> 09:14.953
    Who are you looking for?

09:16.290 --> 09:18.790
       Um, somebody called
        Dixie and Jimmy...

09:18.792 --> 09:19.925
        Dixie and Jimmy.

09:21.261 --> 09:22.794
        Do you know them?

09:22.796 --> 09:24.796
     JOHNNY: Not many people
     go out there.

09:24.798 --> 09:26.331
   You're looking for a horse?

09:27.267 --> 09:28.567
            A horse?

09:28.569 --> 09:30.001
               No.

09:30.003 --> 09:33.104
      They take in horses,
      horses nobody wants.

09:35.075 --> 09:36.341
       That's real noble.

09:37.778 --> 09:39.945
          Where is it?

09:39.947 --> 09:42.581
     JOHNNY: When you get to
        the church there,
         you make a left.

09:42.583 --> 09:45.283
     Keep going a short way,
          you'll see it.

09:46.687 --> 09:50.155
      The Beautiful Place,
    that's what it's called.

09:51.091 --> 09:53.725
      -The Beautiful Place?
              -Yeah.

09:54.828 --> 09:57.796
 Big gates, The Beautiful Place.

09:59.866 --> 10:01.066
       You can't miss it.

10:34.401 --> 10:36.968
        [WIND WHOOSHING]

10:36.970 --> 10:40.038
      [SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

11:54.848 --> 11:56.881
       MAN: You're looking
         for the museum?

12:03.990 --> 12:05.290
    You wanna see the horses?

12:12.332 --> 12:13.398
           Follow me.

12:18.905 --> 12:21.740
     You'll have to wait till
    I tell Dixie you're here.

12:21.742 --> 12:24.909
 She likes to turn the lights on
     and get all prettied up.

12:24.911 --> 12:26.277
   It's all part of the show.

12:34.454 --> 12:37.522
      [SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

13:36.116 --> 13:37.315
         ADELINE: Um...

13:42.055 --> 13:43.555
    DIXIE: What's your name?

13:46.126 --> 13:47.559
         Adeline Winter.

13:47.561 --> 13:49.227
         Adeline Winter?

13:50.864 --> 13:53.097
      Do you know somebody
       called Jack Winter?

13:54.100 --> 13:55.600
    We were famous, you know?

13:56.570 --> 13:58.303
        Um, are you sure

13:58.305 --> 14:01.105
          you don't know
   someone called Jack Winter?

14:01.107 --> 14:02.874
  JIMMY: Who was that you said?

14:02.876 --> 14:04.509
     The name you just said?

14:04.511 --> 14:08.379
  Jack Winter, do you know him?

14:08.381 --> 14:09.614
         No, no, no, no.

14:11.017 --> 14:13.384
  Please, stay a little while.

14:13.386 --> 14:15.620
        Dixie, you should
      be getting some rest.

14:15.622 --> 14:19.290
    I think I made a mistake.
   I'm sorry that I intruded.

14:19.292 --> 14:21.893
          Please, Jimmy,
        tell her to stay.

14:21.895 --> 14:24.996
       -I could come back.
          -DIXIE: Yeah.

14:28.101 --> 14:30.201
      Sorry, you caught us
         at a bad time.

14:31.571 --> 14:33.371
   I shouldn't have intruded.

14:36.943 --> 14:38.443
       You will come back,
            won't you?

14:42.616 --> 14:44.449
         Maybe I can look
       at the visitors log

14:44.451 --> 14:46.951
  and see if your dad was here.

14:46.953 --> 14:49.254
[SOFT SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

14:53.627 --> 14:55.326
  How did you know who he was?

14:56.263 --> 14:57.562
          Just a guess.

15:02.636 --> 15:08.973
  Sure make Dixie happy if you
  came on back, it sure would.

15:13.313 --> 15:14.379
             Please.

15:15.916 --> 15:18.516
        [WIND WHOOSHING]

15:24.224 --> 15:25.456
        [CAR DOOR CLOSES]

15:25.458 --> 15:27.492
       [CAR ENGINE STARTS]

15:43.076 --> 15:45.009
        Dixie and Jimmy.

15:50.583 --> 15:53.418
        [WIND WHOOSHING]

15:56.456 --> 15:59.457
        They're coming to
    take this place from us.

15:59.459 --> 16:01.125
     We have to stay, Jimmy.

16:02.662 --> 16:04.362
      How will she find us?

16:05.999 --> 16:07.732
          I don't know,
    I don't know what to do.

16:12.672 --> 16:15.106
     JIMMY: I can't save us,
     I don't know how.

16:53.613 --> 16:55.580
    Sure glad you came back.

16:57.384 --> 17:01.786
        My father and I,
  we looked for gold together.

17:01.788 --> 17:03.521
     Did you ever find any?

17:04.491 --> 17:06.324
               No.

17:06.326 --> 17:08.226
     Well, you gotta keep on
         looking for it.

17:09.628 --> 17:11.329
      That's what he said.

17:11.330 --> 17:13.131
          Smart fella.

17:13.133 --> 17:15.599
     He told me to find you.

17:15.602 --> 17:18.669
     Well, maybe your daddy
 knows something we don't know.

17:22.409 --> 17:24.709
    Did he actually tell you
        to come out here?

17:27.547 --> 17:29.080
       He left me a note.

17:29.449 --> 17:30.782
             A note?

17:32.585 --> 17:33.684
              Yes.

17:34.754 --> 17:36.354
         After he died.

17:40.226 --> 17:42.060
          Oh, my Lord.

17:43.129 --> 17:45.396
        You did know him.

17:45.398 --> 17:47.799
        No, I didn't know
       your daddy at all.

17:49.369 --> 17:53.071
     Do you know my mother,
          Betty Winter?

17:55.308 --> 17:56.741
          No, I don't.

17:58.344 --> 18:00.211
   Does she know you're here?

18:08.788 --> 18:09.854
            Come in.

18:32.145 --> 18:35.179
       I have that picture
           in my room.

18:35.181 --> 18:36.447
    My mother gave it to me.

18:37.517 --> 18:39.250
DIXIE: I'm waiting for someone.

18:40.220 --> 18:41.586
         ADELINE: You're
      waiting for someone?

18:43.389 --> 18:44.822
         Please help me.

18:45.725 --> 18:47.458
       It's gonna be okay.

18:52.265 --> 18:54.032
      You have to help me.

18:54.033 --> 18:55.800
        No one's coming,
    and we can't hang around
           any longer.

18:59.639 --> 19:01.906
        Please, help me.

19:04.144 --> 19:06.611
       What... Who are you
           waiting for?

19:06.613 --> 19:09.380
        She won't survive
     leaving here, you know?

19:10.383 --> 19:12.583
        She said she was
      waiting for someone.

19:12.585 --> 19:13.918
         Aren't we all?

19:13.920 --> 19:15.386
          [DOG BARKING]

19:37.410 --> 19:38.810
        JIMMY: I got it,
         I'll handle it.

19:38.811 --> 19:40.211
         MR. HEATHERTON:
     We put together a pretty
    big offer for you people,

19:40.213 --> 19:42.747
        and an offer that
       might help you out

19:42.749 --> 19:45.750
     with some of the strain
       you've been feeling
          from the bank.

19:48.221 --> 19:51.422
        We understand it,
 it'll help us out of our home.

19:53.359 --> 19:55.593
         MR. HEATHERTON:
         We're gonna need
    a signature on that sale.

19:55.595 --> 19:57.562
               No.

19:57.563 --> 19:59.530
  It's time you folks moved off
       of this trailer park

19:59.532 --> 20:02.333
       and into some place
        more respectable.

20:02.335 --> 20:04.669
        Jimmy, you folks
        will be evicted.

20:13.880 --> 20:16.948
       [VOICES WHISPERING]

20:17.517 --> 20:20.284
          [DOG BARKING]

20:23.423 --> 20:26.390
       [THUNDER CRASHING]

20:53.786 --> 20:55.553
      There's more, Addie.

20:58.858 --> 21:02.393
       I have learned that
    this experience of death

21:02.395 --> 21:05.329
     is a reflection of how
      we've treated others.

21:25.618 --> 21:28.486
         MR. HEATHERTON:
       Ma'am, we're gonna
       need those papers.

21:31.624 --> 21:33.291
      Let's get this done.

21:42.769 --> 21:45.636
         It's all right.
         We can do this.

21:47.040 --> 21:48.706
        Don't sign that.

21:50.677 --> 21:51.976
        Don't sign these.

21:54.080 --> 21:55.980
        You need to leave
       these people alone.

21:58.685 --> 21:59.817
               Go!

22:09.896 --> 22:12.496
       You will be evicted
     and you will be sorry.

22:16.336 --> 22:17.601
            Come on.

22:17.603 --> 22:20.671
      [CAR ENGINE STARTING]

22:49.836 --> 22:52.503
       DIXIE: Who are you?

22:52.505 --> 22:55.439
   It's just, it's not right,
         and that's all.

22:56.642 --> 23:00.411
     I have to go home now,
  but I'll be back, I promise.

23:08.955 --> 23:11.455
      [CAR ENGINE STARTING]

23:38.518 --> 23:39.583
              Mom?

23:43.423 --> 23:45.089
       Mom, are you here?

24:02.108 --> 24:04.475
        JACK: <i> Your mother</i>
     <i> was always so fearful</i>

24:04.477 --> 24:06.076
<i> that I would leave her one day.</i>

24:17.490 --> 24:19.957
       <i> I tried so hard</i>
    <i> to take her fear away.</i>

24:30.036 --> 24:32.069
   <i> And I couldn't help her.</i>

25:01.767 --> 25:05.903
        Funny, I thought
     they'd be dead by now.

25:14.080 --> 25:15.846
       They gave me away.

25:22.255 --> 25:26.790
   I waited for them every day
         to come get me.

25:30.563 --> 25:32.096
      But they never came.

25:37.203 --> 25:41.238
        And those people
         that raised me,
         those monsters,

25:45.545 --> 25:47.111
   they cared nothing for me.

25:54.053 --> 25:56.020
       I don't understand.

26:02.995 --> 26:04.628
         I was adopted.

26:07.066 --> 26:08.632
    They're my grandparents.

26:17.009 --> 26:18.676
  They don't know who you are?

26:21.180 --> 26:23.280
             It's you
    they've been waiting for.

26:25.217 --> 26:27.251
    -They're waiting for you.
            -I can't.

26:28.921 --> 26:30.588
      Don't go back there.

26:32.658 --> 26:35.826
       I couldn't take it,
         not now, please.

26:39.899 --> 26:41.231
         It's too late.

26:43.035 --> 26:45.269
  They don't know who you are.

26:47.840 --> 26:50.240
 Look at me, please, look at me.

26:53.279 --> 26:55.379
  They don't know who you are.

26:58.250 --> 26:59.850
             Please.

27:17.003 --> 27:20.070
     JACK: <i> But I always knew</i>
<i> they were somehow calling her.</i>

27:23.309 --> 27:25.876
       <i> I tried so hard</i>
<i> to convince her to go to them,</i>

27:25.878 --> 27:27.378
       <i> but she wouldn't.</i>

27:28.414 --> 27:30.014
        <i> Fear, I guess.</i>

28:14.060 --> 28:17.094
   MAN: I am so sorry, Addie.

28:17.096 --> 28:21.298
        I knew your daddy
       since he was born,
          a long time.

28:22.968 --> 28:26.970
     He set up this account
        years ago for you

28:26.972 --> 28:30.441
      and it's at $25,000.

28:32.344 --> 28:35.012
  He used to say how you wanted

28:35.014 --> 28:41.051
            to open up
    a trapeze school one day.

28:41.053 --> 28:43.287
         [LAUGHS] There's
        no money in that.

28:44.356 --> 28:47.124
      My father worked hard
         for that money,

28:47.126 --> 28:48.425
   and that's what he wanted.

28:49.895 --> 28:50.961
              Sure.

29:17.923 --> 29:20.090
         MR. HEATHERTON:
     I'll take care of this.

29:21.961 --> 29:23.861
      Can I help you, miss?

29:26.365 --> 29:30.167
  I'd like to pay what is owed
     on the museum property.

29:30.169 --> 29:33.036
         MR. HEATHERTON:
         Say that again?

29:33.038 --> 29:38.475
          I said I'd...
  I'd like to pay what is owed
       on 110 Wilde Road.

29:38.477 --> 29:45.149
        Well, total owing
          is $48,404.53.

29:45.151 --> 29:47.084
         I have 25,000.

29:47.086 --> 29:49.019
  But that's not what's owing.

29:50.956 --> 29:52.556
        Now I'll tell you
       what I'm gonna do.

29:52.558 --> 29:54.291
 I'm gonna take your good money

29:55.828 --> 29:59.096
     but then you got 21 days
    to come up with the rest.

30:11.010 --> 30:14.978
        You have 21 days,
         not a day more.

30:33.899 --> 30:35.432
   Never knew they had family.

30:37.837 --> 30:39.069
         I'm not family.

30:54.353 --> 30:55.485
          Who sent you?

30:58.123 --> 30:59.356
           My father.

31:02.194 --> 31:03.927
 He said there was a gold mine.

31:05.564 --> 31:07.364
 Not a lot of people know that.

31:32.424 --> 31:33.657
          DIXIE: Jimmy?

31:33.659 --> 31:35.525
   No, it's me, it's Adeline.

31:36.428 --> 31:37.895
         DIXIE: Come in.

31:57.283 --> 31:59.950
     It's still not too late
      to take up the offer.

32:02.154 --> 32:03.620
          I don't wanna
      mess this up for you.

32:04.523 --> 32:06.523
  Why are you helping us, dear?

32:07.092 --> 32:08.258
          Who are you?

32:11.931 --> 32:14.531
     I just don't wanna see
   this place taken from you.

32:18.003 --> 32:19.369
      We have to stay here.

32:21.440 --> 32:23.407
       I'm waiting for her
    to come up this driveway.

32:23.409 --> 32:24.975
      I've waited so long.

32:26.612 --> 32:29.579
         And if we leave,
     she will never find us.

32:31.951 --> 32:36.620
  And I just wanted to believe
     a miracle could happen.

32:40.225 --> 32:41.959
      Miracles can happen.

32:42.661 --> 32:44.194
        I know they can.

32:48.367 --> 32:51.201
 JACK: <i> I always wanted for her</i>
     <i> to meet these people,</i>

32:52.404 --> 32:55.205
         <i> because then</i>
 <i> she'd find out about herself.</i>

32:59.044 --> 33:02.379
<i> She knows her mother and father</i>
       <i> deep in her heart.</i>

33:04.216 --> 33:07.718
        <i> She will always</i>
    <i> have a memory of them,</i>
           <i> we all do.</i>

33:22.334 --> 33:24.401
       Why don't you just
        leave them alone?

33:24.403 --> 33:27.237
      Lady, this place will
       go into foreclosure.

33:27.239 --> 33:28.705
  Nothing I can do about that.

33:29.708 --> 33:31.441
          No, it won't.

33:31.443 --> 33:33.010
       Say what you like.

33:34.546 --> 33:36.513
  There's no gold buried here.

33:36.515 --> 33:38.382
  Now what makes you say that?

33:42.388 --> 33:44.688
          You will not
       get this property.

33:46.125 --> 33:48.191
            Now leave
    before I call the police.

33:50.062 --> 33:52.195
            [LAUGHS]

33:58.103 --> 34:00.570
      [CAR ENGINE STARTING]

34:26.364 --> 34:28.065
     JACK: <i> Stay up, Adeline.</i>

34:30.835 --> 34:32.101
           <i> Stay up.</i>

34:39.143 --> 34:40.610
     JOHNNY: <i> So you're all</i>
          <i> show folk.</i>

35:03.802 --> 35:07.571
       ADELINE: My mother
         has blond hair,
         just like you.

35:08.874 --> 35:11.475
        It'd mean so much
        to have a family.

35:12.411 --> 35:14.644
       This is my family,
          all of this.

35:15.814 --> 35:19.649
     We collected all these
       pieces of wreckage.

35:19.651 --> 35:23.186
      We saved every piece
         like treasure.

35:24.756 --> 35:28.525
   They made up for everything
      that we couldn't save,

35:29.595 --> 35:30.894
          Jimmy and me.

35:41.673 --> 35:44.207
        Why did you choose
     to play Marilyn Monroe?

35:51.783 --> 35:54.718
        People back then,
    they used to think of her

35:54.720 --> 35:57.387
    as just a piece of flesh.

35:57.389 --> 36:00.323
       But she was so much
         more than that.

36:00.325 --> 36:04.628
 She was a bright, bright light
      dressed as a person,

36:04.630 --> 36:08.331
 a bright beautiful lost person.

36:11.603 --> 36:12.836
       Jimmy used to sing.

36:12.838 --> 36:13.904
            [LAUGHS]

36:13.906 --> 36:16.773
 Yeah, Jimmy was a great singer.

36:16.775 --> 36:18.775
     And I would be Marilyn.

36:29.388 --> 36:31.254
          [DOG BARKING]

36:31.256 --> 36:32.556
         It's all right.

36:50.776 --> 36:52.976
         JIMMY: What you
       got there, Johnny?

36:52.978 --> 36:54.744
           Did you know
     she does the high wire?

36:57.683 --> 36:58.815
        Did she tell you?

37:00.919 --> 37:02.586
  Maybe people wanna see that.

37:04.556 --> 37:05.622
            I would.

37:06.758 --> 37:08.325
     JIMMY: Well, I'll be...

37:11.830 --> 37:13.897
   We need to bring the people
        out there, Jimmy.

37:18.370 --> 37:21.638
      DIXIE: Up in the air
     on a wire, imagine it.

37:22.608 --> 37:24.374
         JIMMY: Sure love
        to see you do it.

37:27.446 --> 37:29.613
      ADELINE: <i> I don't know</i>
    <i> if I can do it anymore.</i>

37:31.984 --> 37:35.385
  <i> My father was always there</i>
          <i> by my side.</i>

37:38.790 --> 37:41.591
       JACK: <i> Our memories</i>
         <i> of who we are</i>

37:41.593 --> 37:44.361
      <i> run in our blood</i>
   <i> and through our hearts.</i>

37:44.896 --> 37:46.529
   <i> And she remembered them.</i>

37:53.705 --> 37:57.040
    DIXIE: <i> Something very bad</i>
   <i> happened to me and Jimmy.</i>

37:58.377 --> 37:59.576
       <i> It was her light.</i>

38:02.614 --> 38:04.648
 DIXIE:
 She was there waiting for me.

38:05.884 --> 38:08.885
   I could disappear into her

38:08.887 --> 38:11.521
        and leave behind
     the person that I was.

38:21.066 --> 38:23.500
          Why would you
        want to do that?

38:33.945 --> 38:36.379
      I gave away my child,

38:37.983 --> 38:40.383
   a child I loved and wanted.

38:40.952 --> 38:42.652
       It broke who I was.

38:44.723 --> 38:46.723
  I had to become someone else.

38:51.530 --> 38:55.832
        I had a baby girl,
